snippet.textDisplay: Ok, on one hand I'm happy that this show is going on cartoon network and boomerang cause now i can watch more of Lucas's adorableness as well as everyone else in the world but, on the other hand i'm kinda scared because the last time a popular show on YouTube got their fist big break, they were shortly pulled off the air and never heard from again, both from television AND from the internet(as far as i know anyway🤔). I mean it happened to YouTube shows like "Annoying Orange" and "Fred", both started on YouTube, both were popular had over one million subscribers, but then got their own TV series(cartoon network for Annoying Orange, Nickelodeon for Fred). 1 to 2 seasons (and 3 Fred Movies) later....Cancelled due negative ratings and poor reviews from critics(I mean Lucas Cruikshank aka Fred made another show called "Marvin Marvin" but that also got cancelled after 1 season). I'm sorry, maybe I'm being too pessimistic. I honestly wish Lucas the best and I really hope that both Cartoon network and Boomerang take good care of him, since I have and watch both channels, i'll be sure to eye out. ;) I look forward to seeing Lucas's new chapter in life and who knows? Maybe it'll turn out better than expected! I mean not all YouTube shows bite the dust the moment they go on television! Show like Adventure Time and Rick and Morty both started online and they're still going strong! (even after the Adventure time series ended) This show will possibly fit that category too! Best of luck! and Congrats! ^_^
